Issue 77. (semantic) stop ignoring default attributes (e.g. from DTD)
Thread:
  http://www.w3.org/mid/4.3.2.7.2.20031008173446.01709bf8@172.27.10.30 (issue)
  http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-style/2003Oct/0029.html (reply)
  http://www.w3.org/mid/200310131858.36221.roger.larsson@incrementa.se (issue)
  http://www.w3.org/mid/200310132109.h9DL96B01219@djwhome.demon.co.uk (reply to second issue)
  http://www.w3.org/mid/69421B63-FE02-11D7-8E9F-003065B8CF0E@iki.fi (response to first reply, needs reply)
  http://www.w3.org/mid/78A033BB-FE02-11D7-8E9F-003065B8CF0E@iki.fi (response to second reply, needs reply)
  http://www.w3.org/mid/170A2352-0259-11D8-9167-003065B8CF0E@iki.fi (needs reply)
  http://www.w3.org/mid/200310200620.h9K6KTl00612@djwhome.demon.co.uk
  http://www.w3.org/mid/338C56E6-0323-11D8-B18E-003065B8CF0E@iki.fi
  http://www.w3.org/mid/3FE9F445.50701@w3.org (XMLCG request on this issue, probably needs reply)

Resolution: Add text to the effect of:

   For external subsets: Not require that UAs read the DTD, handle the
   same as standalone document. (This is the <a>XML spec's conformance
   requirements</a>.)

   For internal namespace knowledge (e.g. HTML and XHTML UAs that do
   not read the HTML or XHTML DTDs but know what they contain): Not
   require that UAs treat attributes as present unless present in
   markup.

   For internal subsets: Require that UAs treat attributes as present
   even if not present in markup (as <a>required by XML</a>).

   Note: Typically implementations choose to ignore external subsets.

Document updated.
Reply: http://www.w3.org/mid/16426.37669.140608.891338@lanalana.inria.fr
Issue closed.
