Issue 103. Interaction of run-in with anonymous block boxes.
Comment: http://www.w3.org/mid/20031011130232.GA3710@tapir
Comment: http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-style/2000May/0010.html
Comment: http://www.w3.org/mid/20031011235501.GA2332@tapir

Resolution: three changes:
1. a run-in box cannot run in to a block into which a later box
   also runs in
2. run-in cannot run into a run-in
3. change "In other words: if a block box (such as that generated for
   the DIV above) has another block box inside it (such as the P
   above), then we force it to have only block boxes inside it, by
   wrapping any inline boxes in an anonymous block box." in 9.2.1 to:
   "In other words: if a block box (such as that generated for the DIV
   above) has another block box or a run-in box inside it (such as the
   P above), then we force it to have only block boxes or run-in boxes."
Reply: http://www.w3.org/mid/16427.61245.156261.190240@lanalana.inria.fr
Document updated.
Issue closed.
