Issue 192. http://www.w3.org/mid/3F94ED7C.8070206@escape.com

# margin-top, margin-bottom
# Applies to: all elements but inline, non-replaced elements and
#             internal table elements

Any reason why it doesn't need to apply to inline, non-replaced
elements? Borders and padding do; they just don't have an effect
on line-height calculation. Since that seems to be the rationale
for excluding it, I'd just combine the definitions for all margins
and leave the no-effect part to the inline model explanation.

Resolution: Assumed disagreement by Ian, David, Bert. Vertical margins
don't apply to non-replaced inlines because they have absolutely no
effect, and it is easier to explain this by saying "they don't apply"
than "well they apply, they just don't do anything".
http://www.w3.org/mid/20031120004949.GA10250@darby.dbaron.org
Reply: http://www.w3.org/mid/200402131739.i1DHdqfT030524@lanalana.inria.fr
Issue closed.
