Issue 200. http://www.w3.org/mid/020A3CF87FB5AC47AA67966B33845755069BA20A@xboi22.boise.itc.hp.com
|
| Neither the CSS2 or the CSS2.1 specifications address vertical-align
| <length> in section 17.5.3 Table height Algorithms.
|
| Is there a reason for omitting <length> and <percentage>?  If so, CSS2.1
| should state why these values of vertical-align are not appropriate.
|
| If this is a oversight, I think the spec should say that they have their
| meanings as defined.

Bert says:
I think it is indeed an oversight that nothing is said about
'vertical-align: <length>|<percentage>' for tables. And I think it
should say that it does nothing and is interpreted as 'baseline' (the
initial value). It should say this in 17.5.3.

Resolution: We should say it does the same as baseline.
Document updated.
