Issue 203. http://www.w3.org/mid/B2901A91-05A3-11D8-A7F5-000A958E6110@apple.com

Hyatt says: Does first-letter apply only to block flows like
list-items, table cells, and blocks? I'd prefer it if it did, i.e., if
it was applicable only to the same set of elements that first-line is
applicable to. It doesn't make sense to me to apply it to inlines,
since an inline element could be right in the middle of a word. The
term "first-letter" sort of loses its meaning if it could be applied
to inlines.

Tantek says: I think first-letter can make sense in many inline
contexts, like the start of a sentence. I have seen the first-letter
of some inline spans (like words) boldened in a few instances in some
publications. In CSS3 Selectors we made the deliberate choice to allow
first-letter to apply to *all elements* for this reason. However, for
CSS2.1 I am fine with saying that :first-letter, like :first-line, can
only be attached to a block-level element. See
http://tantek.com/w3c/css/inlinefirstletter.html for tests and
results.

Ian says: I think we should make apply only to blocks in 2.1 too.

Bert says: No opinion.

Resolution: Doesn't apply to inlines in 2.1
Document updated.
Issue closed.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Issue 204. http://www.w3.org/mid/B2901A91-05A3-11D8-A7F5-000A958E6110@apple.com

Hyatt says: Do first-line and first-letter cross from blocks into
inline blocks? For the former, I'd say "No", since that doesn't make
much sense, and so i'd like to say "No" for first-letter as well in
order to be consistent.

<div><span style="display:inline-block">Hello</span></div>

In the above, I'd like a first-letter/line style on the div not to
apply to "Hello" at all.

Tantek says: Proposed resolution: Accept. I agree that descendant
inline-blocks (and floats and positioned elements and tables and table
cells etc.) should *not* get first-line(letter) styling from a block
parent whose first-line(letter) was selected. See
http://tantek.com/w3c/css/firstlinefloatinlineblock.html for tests of
first-line in particular and results.

Resolution: Agreed. :first-line doesn't _apply_ to the inline-block
(you stop propagating the "pseudo-elementness" when you hit a line
box, basically, so :first-line only applies to one line). (Note,
however, that we don't define if styles set on the :first-line should
/inherit/ into inline-blocks on the first line. That's undefined in
2.1 because we don't know what is best yet.)
Document updated.
Issue closed.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
