Issue 236.
emeyer writes:
| In CSS2.1, section 17.2.1 talks about inserting anonymous objects in
| various scenarios, but it doesn't mention table-caption elements.  If
| I'm reading rule 5 correctly, then an anonymous table-row object should
| be inserted between a table-caption element and its parent table
| element.  Is that correct?
|
| The way I read the rules, the following markup:
|
|     <table>
|      <caption>ick</caption>
|      ...blah blah blah...
|     </table>
|
| ...should result in an anonymous table-row element being inserted
| between the table and the caption, thanks to rule #5, which doesn't
| list table-caption elements as one of the types that avoids the
| triggering of said rule.
|     Furthermore, if I'm correct, given the following:
|
|     <table>
|      <caption>ick</caption>
|      <td>yuck</td>
|     </table>
|
| ...then a single table-row should enclose the caption and cell
| together.  Am I overlooking something?

Resolution: add 'table-caption', 'table-column', and
'table-column-group' to rule 5 in section 17.2.1 Anonymous table
objects. Add 'table-header-group', 'table-footer-group' to rule 2 at
the end of the list of parts after "is not a".
Document updated.
