Issue 267. http://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=225811#c14

CSS2.1 says "A descendent box is positioned absolutely, partly outside
the box. Such boxes are not clipped by the overflow property on their
ancestors." (section 11.1) but also says " It affects the clipping of
all of the element's content except any descendant elements (and their
respective content and descendants) whose containing block is the
viewport or an ancestor of the element." (section 11.1.1)

I believe the first quote above should have the second sentence
changed to "Such boxes are not always clipped by the overflow property
on their ancestors." (addition of "always"), leaving the later section
to define it properly.

Resolution: Agreed.
Document updated.
Issue closed.
