Issue P3. http://www.w3.org/mid/3FF6FF3C.3050004@mit.edu
There is a number of places in the spec where terms are used without
linking to the term definition.  For example the "Applies To" part of
hte "max-width" property says "all elements except non-replaced inline
elements and table elements".  None of this is linkified; the user is
left to guess what "table elements" are in this context.  These are
actually defined at http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/tables.html#internal but
that's not made clear anywhere in the spec apart from the Index.  I've
seen at least one WG member be confused as to the meaning of "table
element" in the CSS2.1 spec as a result....

It would be good to make both "table elements" and "non-replaced inline
elements" links in that text and in all similar texts in the spec.

Rejected.
Editors can fix if they see it.
Issue closed.
