Issue 276. 10.3.5 Floating, non-replaced elements
# Thirdly, find the available width: in this case, this is the width
# of the containing block minus 'margin-left' and 'margin-right'.

That should be "minus the used values of 'margin-left',
'border-left-width', 'padding-left', 'padding-right',
'border-right-width', 'margin-right', and the widths of any relevant
scroll bars".

Resolution: agreed.
Document updated.
Issue closed.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Issue 277. 10.4 Minimum and maximum widths: 'min-width' and 'max-width'

If you have a 300x375 image, with 'height' and 'width' both set to
'auto', and:

   min-width: 75
   max-width: 150
   min-height: 0
   max-height: 75

...the current rules in section 10.4 end up saying that the dimensions
should be 150x75, which is much more skewed than it should be. The
better answer would be 75x75.

dbaron says:
|
| I propose the following two changes be made to both sections 10.3.2
| and 10.6.2, no matter what we decide for section 10.4, to clarify things
| that I noticed I had to implement that were defined poorly or not at
| all:
|
|   1. In sections 10.3.2 (PROP=width, OTHER=height) and 10.6.2
|      (PROP=height, OTHER=width), change the text:
|
|        If 'PROP' has a computed value of 'auto' and 'OTHER' also has a
|        computed value of 'auto', the element's intrinsic PROP is the
|        used value of 'PROP'.
|
|      to:
|
|        If 'PROP' has a computed value of 'auto' and 'OTHER' also has a
|        computed value of 'auto', the used value of 'PROP' is determined
|        by the <a href="the rules in section 10.4">as described in the
|        section on min-width</a>.
|
|   2. To the end of sections 10.3.2 and 10.6.2, add:
|
|      Note: The used OTHER is influenced by the computed values of
|      'min-OTHER' and 'max-OTHER'.
|
| Proposal (1) resolves a contradiction between 10.3.2/10.6.2 and 10.4
| (where we clearly want 10.4 to win), and proposal (2) clarifies the case
| where one is 'auto' and the other is not.

fantasai proposed the following table to replace the current list in
section 10.4:
   http://fantasai.inkedblade.net/style/specs/css2.1/min-max-replaced

dbaron implemented this and it passed the relevant tests.

Document updated.
Issue closed.
