Issue 282. need to update text at top of section 6.1.
It reads:

| The final value of a property is the result of a three-step
| calculation: the value is determined through specification (the
| "specified value"), then resolved into an absolute value if
| necessary (the "computed value"), and finally transformed according
| to the limitations of the local environment (the "actual value").

It should read:

| The final value of a property is the result of a four-step
| calculation: the value is determined through specification (the
| "specified value"), then resolved into a value that is used for
| inheritance (the computed value), then converted into an absolute
| value if necessary (the "used value"), and finally transformed
| according to the limitations of the local environment (the "actual
| value").

Document updated.
Issue closed.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Issue 283. http://www.w3.org/mid/200402162226.i1GMQ0n01266@djwhome.demon.co.uk
C.2.18 says that aural style sheets have been moved to an
informative appendix.  I interpreted this to mean that they
had been deferred pending interoperable implementations,
so didn't look at Appendix A in detail.

However, A.1 says:
 1) that they are deprecated, which is much stronger than
    simply being deferred;
 2) says they are *defined* by the appendix, which seems very
    normative to me (this is an internal conflict in Appendix
    A as well as between Appendix A and Appendix C.

Resolution: Change appendix C to say appendix A is deprecated.
Issue closed.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Issue P18 [284]. http://www.w3.org/mid/16428.57705.189337.320274@lanalana.inria.fr

We decided that Fantasai was right and the example in 9.8.3, showing
'clear' on an inline element, was wrong. But we didn't remove the
example:

    Resolution: The example is indeed inaccurate, but we're going to
    leave it for now.

I'm not too happy with that. Can't we remove 9.8, or add some text to
it, that says the example is wrong?

Issue rejected.
Issue closed.
